title: Girls Soccer Roundup for Tuesday, Oct. 20
text:

Posted! A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. Join the Conversation Simeon Pincus, @SimeonPincus 6:48 p.m. EDT October 20, 2015 Girls soccer 13 CONNECT 17 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Scotch Plains-Fanwood 3, Oak Knoll 0: Annie Pierce netted two goals and Kerri McNeely hit once as Scotch Plains-Fanwood stayed undefeated. Andrea Leitner made four saves for the Raiders (15-0-1), who have been scored on just once this season. 
Plainfield 4, Somerset Tech 0: Four-year starter Keyanna Bagley celebrated senior day with a goal and an assist and Sheilah Sarpong led the way with a hat trick as Plainfield improved to 4-9. Angel Branch posted two saves for the Cardinals shutout, while Kaycie Sconda stopped 12 shots for Somerset Tech (6-13). 
Rutgers Prep 6, Bound Brook 4: Sophie Thellmann netted a hat trick, while Grance Bancone and Chiara Tibbit added goals for Rutgers Prep. Christina Mayorga notched a hat trick of her own for Bound Brook, who also got one from Nicole Jiminez. 
Bernards 5, Mount St. Mary 0: Claudia Prandoni scored two goals, while Lauren McHale, Francesca Porambo and Makenna Davis also hit for Bernards. 
Gill St. Bernard’s 3, North Plainfield 3: Sam Delehanty, Hayley Goldin and Amelia Kirby scored goals, while Jane O’Conner provided two assists as Gill St. Bernard’s earned a draw. Ashley Atubi finished with two goals and an assist, while Caitlin Gugliotta added a goal and an assist for North Plainfield. 
Watchung Hills 2, Montgomery 0: Gianna Alfano and Melanie Cunha scored goals, and Brooke Stanicki made five saves to power Watchung Hills (9-5-3). Breanna Cocuzzo made 16 saves for Montgomery (3-12). 
Hunterdon Central 4, Pingry 0: Luciana Zullo netted two goals, while Brianna Floyd and Hannah Merlo each scored once to fuel Hunterdon Central. Charlotte Curnin made 11 saves for Pingry. 
Belvidere 6, Manville 1: Mariana Munoz scored for Manville. 
Immaculata 2, Voorhees 2: Kathleen Mulkerin tallied a goal and an assist for Immaculata (0-10-1). Teri Jackson also scored. For Voorhees (4-7-2), Katie Schweikert and Natalie Diaz scored. Elizabeth Jardinella and Claire Furino each chipped in an assist. 13 CONNECT 17 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://mycj.co/1LJhNUN TOP VIDEOS
